item.dc:creator: @file824ph file824ph
item.description:
@file824ph wrote:

well i found it to be the push in teh direction i needed,
i nearly have it working right now

[quote=“bundy, post:81, topic:265915”][quote author=peterbjornx link=topic=351106.msg2744342#msg2744342 date=1239546746]
If he wants a new region, he needs to modify the versionlists , all he now does is fucking up the selected map.
[/quote]

Ah, the versionlist archive. You have to make sure it’s ehm, ‘up-to-date’, by adding the new entries into it [map_index contains appropriate landscape file id, map file id, and whether or not it is members only, and area ID. map_crc contains CRCs on map files, and map_version contains the file versions :)].[/quote]

i have a feeling this just got alot more complicated
either way im sure ill get it eventuly,
and (of course) i assume the map editor doesnt do
this by default and ill need to add it in?
